	<gx:CascadingStyle kml:id="__managed_style_2C8B1219A73E916505BC">
		<Style>
			<IconStyle>
				<scale>1.2</scale>
				<Icon>
					<href>https://earth.google.com/earth/document/icon?color=1976d2&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=4</href>
				</Icon>
				<hotSpot x="64" y="128" xunits="pixels" yunits="insetPixels"/>
			</IconStyle>
			<LabelStyle>
			</LabelStyle>
			<LineStyle>
				<color>ff2dc0fb</color>
				<width>3</width>
			</LineStyle>
			<PolyStyle>
				<color>40ffffff</color>
			</PolyStyle>
			<BalloonStyle>
				<text>Macka&apos;s Tomb
🚫
GPS: -37.848102, 145.043958
MELWAYS REF: 59 F-5
LOCATION: Follow south side of Gardiners Creek upstream from Toorak Road or cross creek via stepping stones.
VALUE: ☹️
ENTRANCE: 1.9 ⚪
WATER: 🙂
OTHER SHAPES: ☹️
TRANSPORT: Glen Waverley train to Tooronga.
CLEANLINESS: Some webs further up.
PROBLEMS: Crossing creek to get in.
HIGHLIGHT: Joins up with Hexadus.
NEARBY: Big Bastard &amp; Hexadus.
CLAN ZONE: east.
NOTES: Much more interesting since being joined up with Hexadus in 2017. Crawl into small crawl pipe not far up on the right hand side then go with flow a short distance into Hexadus. See Hexadus entry for map.
Macka&apos;s is named after the short (in height &amp; length of time in the Clan) member from the late 1980&apos;s.</text>
			</BalloonStyle>
		</Style>
	</gx:CascadingStyle>
	<gx:CascadingStyle kml:id="__managed_style_117D06C6FC3E916505BB">
		<Style>
			<IconStyle>
				<Icon>
					<href>https://earth.google.com/earth/document/icon?color=1976d2&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=4</href>
				</Icon>
				<hotSpot x="64" y="128" xunits="pixels" yunits="insetPixels"/>
			</IconStyle>
			<LabelStyle>
			</LabelStyle>
			<LineStyle>
				<color>ff2dc0fb</color>
				<width>2</width>
			</LineStyle>
			<PolyStyle>
				<color>40ffffff</color>
			</PolyStyle>
			<BalloonStyle>
				<text>Como Falls
🚫 🍸 🧗 👁️
GPS: -37.834723, 145.004043
MELWAYS REF: 2M C-3
LOCATION: Opposite Williams Rd on the south-east bank of the Yarra.
CLAN ZONE: Inner.
ENTRANCE: 2.6m ⚪
OTHER SHAPES: ⚪ Red brick.
CLEANLINESS: 🙂 unless you take the hardcore route.
TRANSPORT: Train to South Yarra &amp; walk or tram 8 to Williams Rd then walk.
HIGHLIGHT: Waterfalls.
VALUE: 🏆
PROBLEMS: Quite long. Hardcore route is low for twenty minutes.
NEARBY: Nylex, No Vest, Punctual, Burnley &amp; South Yarra.
NOTES: Probably the best round drain on the list. Follow arrows to do whole system. After 30 minutes take left small tunnel to see the Wishing Well (which is up a left side tunnel in the left side tunnel) then continue up the small tunnel until you get back to the main system.
Originally known as Yarra Tunnel, Como Falls takes its name from a local park/house as well as its main feature.</text>
				<gx:displayMode>panel</gx:displayMode>
			</BalloonStyle>
		</Style>
	</gx:CascadingStyle>
