			</PolyStyle>
			<BalloonStyle>
				<text>Macka&apos;s Tomb
🚫
GPS: -37.848102, 145.043958
MELWAYS REF: 59 F-5
LOCATION: Follow south side of Gardiners Creek upstream from Toorak Road or cross creek via stepping stones.
VALUE: ☹️
ENTRANCE: 1.9 ⚪
WATER: 🙂
OTHER SHAPES: ☹️
TRANSPORT: Glen Waverley train to Tooronga.
CLEANLINESS: Some webs further up.
PROBLEMS: Crossing creek to get in.
HIGHLIGHT: Joins up with Hexadus.
NEARBY: Big Bastard &amp; Hexadus.
CLAN ZONE: east.
NOTES: Much more interesting since being joined up with Hexadus in 2017. Crawl into small crawl pipe not far up on the right hand side then go with flow a short distance into Hexadus. See Hexadus entry for map.
Macka&apos;s is named after the short (in height &amp; length of time in the Clan) member from the late 1980&apos;s.</text>
			</BalloonStyle>
		</Style>
	</gx:CascadingStyle>
