🚫 🍸 🧗 👁️
GPS: -37.834723, 145.004043
MELWAYS REF: 2M C-3
LOCATION: Opposite Williams Rd on the south-east bank of the Yarra.
CLAN ZONE: Inner.
ENTRANCE: 2.6m ⚪
OTHER SHAPES: ⚪ Red brick.
CLEANLINESS: 🙂 unless you take the hardcore route.
TRANSPORT: Train to South Yarra &amp; walk or tram 8 to Williams Rd then walk.
HIGHLIGHT: Waterfalls.
VALUE: 🏆
PROBLEMS: Quite long. Hardcore route is low for twenty minutes.
NEARBY: Nylex, No Vest, Punctual, Burnley &amp; South Yarra.
NOTES: Probably the best round drain on the list. Follow arrows to do whole system. After 30 minutes take left small tunnel to see the Wishing Well (which is up a left side tunnel in the left side tunnel) then continue up the small tunnel until you get back to the main system.
Originally known as Yarra Tunnel, Como Falls takes its name from a local park/house as well as its main feature.</text>
				<gx:displayMode>panel</gx:displayMode>
			</BalloonStyle>
		</Style>
	</gx:CascadingStyle>
