	<Folder id="5984C714B8000001">
		<name>Melbourne Drains</name>
		<open>1</open>
		<styleUrl>#__managed_style_088AD2C4923E916505AD</styleUrl>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000004">
			<name>Snorkel&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Snorkel’s Tomb<br></div><div>GPS -37.836420, 145.227211<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 63 F-3<br></div><div>LOCATION: South end of Ringwood public golf course on the north bank of Dandenong Creek<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2 × 1.4m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⬜<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Ringwood<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Side entrance<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Lowness<br></div><div>NEARBY: Chastity Belt &amp; Eel Pit<br></div><div>NOTES: Quite a dull drain.<br></div><div>Snorkel is named after a member from the early 90’s.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.227211,-37.83642,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000006">
			<name>South Yarra</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>South Yarra<br></div><div>GPS -37.833832, 144.993516<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 2L J-2<br></div><div>LOCATION: North end of Yarra St on the south bank of the Yarra<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.8m ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: Inner<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕ balloon<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Manhole in right split is a fun (&amp; risky) exit<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to South Yarra<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Small, dirty &amp; wet!<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Muddy walls<br></div><div>⏱ Tidal<br></div><div>NEARBY: Hyley, Albert Pk, Bob’s Tomb, Como Falls and No Vest<br></div><div>NOTES: Was originally called “Shit Shoot” due to the brown rusty mud all over the walls.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.9936339823556,-37.83387522027245,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B800000C">
			<name>Flat</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Flat<br></div><div>GPS -37.799186, 145.115965<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 47 B-4<br></div><div>LOCATION: North end of Box Hill Cres over Belmore Rd<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2 × 1.8m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Ringwood train to Box Hill then bus<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Joining room<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: A bit of rubble at start<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Could be worse. ⭕ 5cm deep<br></div><div>NEARBY: 10th<br></div><div>NOTES: Goes up to 2.1m after the join. Drain just down from outlet is called Spectator.<br></div><div>Song goes a flat tyre riding out to find Flat. Sloth &amp; Woody each got a flat on the first expo.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.115965,-37.799186,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B800000D">
			<name>Flooded</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Flooded<br></div><div>GPS -37.77114, 144.987474<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 30 C-8<br></div><div>LOCATION: Via rectangle M/H on cnr of Osborne St &amp; Sumner Av. 6 min crawl to 3.2 pipe<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: Via a manhole<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕, RRB &amp; mummy<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: South Morang train to Northcote<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: You need to crawl in via small side pipe that gets deeper as you go<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: ☹<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ Chest<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Has no inlet or outlet so just getting in is a highlight<br></div><div>NEARBY: Banger’s, Nam &amp; NGCD<br></div><div>NOTES: A good one if you feel like crawling through a side-pipe to get into an old flooded muddy section of Northcote High Darkie. Can be quite fun if you’re mentally prepared.<br></div><div>Flooded Darkie is named after the fact that… ah, you figure it out.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.987474,-37.77114,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000010">
			<name>Vegie</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Vegie<br></div><div>🚫 🚲<br></div><div>GPS -37.762671, 144.869522<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 27 G-6<br></div><div>LOCATION: Opposite 6 Tea Tree Gardens Drive<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Tram 57 to end of line<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The ramps<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: 130 Steps &amp; Crime Watch<br></div><div>NOTES: Not too far from TWL Bridge Room. Not a very interesting tunnel.<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low pipe.<br></div><div>Vegie has a politically incorrect name… it has a lot of ramps in it… get it? Ramps = wheelchairs = vegies<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.869522,-37.762671,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000011">
			<name>Virgin Web</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Virgin Web<br></div><div>🚫 🔑 👁<br></div><div>GPS -37.749251, 145.135896<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 33 G-2<br></div><div>LOCATION: East side of Fitzsimons Lane south of Lempriere just over fence<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂 Unless you go with flow (no point)<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Bus<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Entrance<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Jumping fence<br></div><div>NEARBY: Fisted<br></div><div>NOTES: Entrance is the only good thing.<br></div><div>Virgin Web had that many webs in it when first explored that it was thought they were the original webs… or something like that?<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.135896,-37.749251,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000012">
			<name>Werribee Slide</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Werribee Slide<br></div><div>🚫 ⏱<br></div><div>GPS -37.919115, 144.657231<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 244 J-1<br></div><div>LOCATION: North east corner of Federation Trail &amp; Werribee River<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South west<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.5m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: Read the Notes &amp; it will be ☹<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The Slide<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Good other than wet<br></div><div>⛔ Thigh deep outlet<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Werribee but car recommended<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Flooded outlet<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>NEARBY: CPND<br></div><div>NOTES: Nice little drain, but don’t do very far past the slide.<br></div><div>Name taken from the suburb &amp; main feature – not because living in Werribee is a slippery slide into a life of crime.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.657231,-37.919115,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000013">
			<name>Windtunnel</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Windtunnel<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.822769, 144.765002<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 39 C-9<br></div><div>LOCATION: East end of Felstead Drive<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.7m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South west<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Muddy/wet<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: None as long as you like RCP<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Watergardens train to Sunshine, then bus to corner of Boundary and Robinsons Roads and then walk<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Grille room<br></div><div>⛔ Thigh-deep at start<br></div><div>NEARBY: Snakepit, Frog’s Hollow, Dodgy’s Tomb &amp; Chocolate Mouse<br></div><div>NOTES: Exit via a manhole where Westpark Drive turns west. Has been extended since the last edition of the DG.<br></div><div>Named Windtunnel because the wind constantly blasting through the drain made it feel like being in a windtunnel and because of Dodgy’s fart.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.765002,-37.822769,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000015">
			<name>Yabbie</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Yabbie<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.746278, 144.791396<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 25 J-2<br></div><div>LOCATION: Opposite 15 Rita St<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.8m ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North west<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Muddy<br></div><div>⛔ Thigh<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Watergardens train to St Albans<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Long, small &amp; boring<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Sometimes has lots of yabbies in it<br></div><div>NEARBY: Alien’s, Marz’s, Slasha’s &amp; Bathory’s<br></div><div>NOTES: There may be some new explorable items in the surrounding areas.<br></div><div>Yabbie usually has yabbies in it.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.791396,-37.746278,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000017">
			<name>Misfit&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Misfit’s Tomb<br></div><div>GPS -38.104673, 144.353402<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.9m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>LOCATION: Look west from Princes Hwy bridge over Cowies Ck<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⬜<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Spa &amp; exit<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Shin deep spa<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car. Train to Geelong &amp; taxi<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Passing spa<br></div><div>NEARBY: Wes’<br></div><div>NOTES: Do not turn back. Go all the way!<br></div><div>Named after the Gold Clannie winner.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.353402,-38.104673,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000018">
			<name>Moe&apos;s Rear End</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Moe’s Rear End<br></div><div>🚫 👁<br></div><div>GPS -38.166928, 146.255119<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>LOCATION: On the left hand side of the house on the bend of Della Torre Rd, Moe<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: GPS<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Right next to house<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>NEARBY: Twisty’s &amp; Chloe’s Moe<br></div><div>NOTES: Has not been explored beyond the GPT<br></div><div>The name comes from the drain being at the rear of the town of Moe.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>146.255119,-38.166928,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B8000019">
			<name>Mouse Hole</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Mouse Hole<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.556367, 143.864239<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.5m ⬜<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>LOCATION: 25a Rowe St<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Slides<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car. Train to Ballarat<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low &amp; slippery in parts<br></div><div>NEARBY: Mira’s &amp; Ballarat<br></div><div>NOTES: The worst of the Ballarat trio but still worth a visit.<br></div><div>Looking out of the drain resembles a mouse hole.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>143.864239,-37.556367,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B800001A">
			<name>Omeo</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Omeo<br></div><div>🚫 🚲<br></div><div>GPS -37.100764, 147.592633<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7 ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>LOCATION: Corner Short St &amp; Great Alpine Road at waterwheel. Do from other end. Easy to find. Only if in area.<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Outlet not recorded but easy to find<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The inlet<br></div><div>NEAREST: Traralgon<br></div><div>NOTES: Short tunnel with grilled off inlet. Local mines while in area.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>147.592633,-37.100764,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B800001B">
			<name>Proper&apos;s Tube</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Proper’s Tube<br></div><div>🍸 🔑<br></div><div>GPS -38.198190, 144.320363<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.4m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>LOCATION: On the east side of Pioneer Rd, south of Waurn Ponds Aquatic Centre<br></div><div>TUNNEL ENDS: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Grille Rooms<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: ☹<br></div><div>⛔ Thigh<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: No manholes<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>NEAREST: Geelong<br></div><div>NOTES: Inlet located at -38.198413, 144.315564 just north of the Colac Rd &amp; Parkwood Dve intersection.<br></div><div>Named after Proper of the Cave Clan.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.320363,-38.19819,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B800001C">
			<name>Seyless</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Seyless<br></div><div>🚲 🌳 🍸 🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.017897, 145.128892<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.9m RCP<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow path to river from where the Goulburn Valley Hwy meets Emily St<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Dunny door<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Lifting dunny door on your own<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>NEAREST: Shepparton<br></div><div>NOTES: Worth a look if you’re stopping for a break.<br></div><div>Was named Seyessa by Flo &amp; Doug in 2013 but renamed Seyless by Thongs in 2017.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.128892,-37.017897,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B800001D">
			<name>Shepparton</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Shepparton<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -36.389074, 145.433678<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: Grilled 2m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>LOCATION: Outlet is buried. Entry via small grille in the southern verge of the Midland Hwy near the Hartwigs truck dealership. Drops into side pipe which is followed by a painful 40 metre crawl<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Flooded / Mud city. Lost both thongs. ⛔ Mainly mud. Flooded outlet<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Grille room<br></div><div>NEAREST: Seyless<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Fairly difficult entry down the side of the embankment. Careful! Use plants etc for support. Fairly difficult.<br></div><div>NOTES: Shit sewer drain but as part of the Shep East Drainage scheme. One nice grille room, but not worth the crawl to get to it. May be better if it gets extended (and mud clears up) or step-irons are ever installed here.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.433678,-36.389074,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
