		<Placemark id="5984C714B9000035">
			<name>Stormdrain 2000 Series</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Stormdrain 2000 Series<br></div><div>🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.688623, 144.987392<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 8 B-10<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow Central Ck against the flow (north) from Mahoneys Rd (-37.691754, 144.982028). First underpass is on the right bank of creek just past the Western Ring Rd.<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: Various<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: Corrugated pipe, ⌒, ⬜ &amp; ⭕<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Keon Park<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Various underpasses<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: ☹ — Probably wet, muddy &amp; shin deep in parts<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Area is overgrown<br></div><div>NEARBY: Kanish’s Tomb, Acorn’s Tomb, Edgar’s Tomb, Dead &amp; Karmein’s<br></div><div>NOTES: This series of underpasses was “OK” at best. We’re hoping that it is slightly better since the Hume Fwy was built. Once you’ve found underpass one (see Location) then walk through the corrugated tunnels to underpass two (-37.688521, 144.986304). Underpass three is located here: -37.688293, 144.988194. There is a drain near here.<br></div><div>Stormdrain 2000 was so-called after Wes &amp; Doug saw dozens of pieces of 2.2m sized corrugated pipes in the late 90’s — they thought it was the drain that would take over in the 21st century so J.T. Draine was coined “Stormdrain 2000 Found!”<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.987392,-37.688623,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714B9000036">
			<name>Success</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Success<br></div><div>🚫 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.876778, 145.185912<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 71 H-1<br></div><div>LOCATION: Located on south side of High St Road opposite Capital Ave<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ×2 ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Room<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Pel Pit<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Getting to the “gets bigger section”<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Glen Waverley then bus to Capital Ave<br></div><div>NOTES: Keep taking the main pipe until it’s annoyingly low (1.4m) &amp; slow it for about half an hour &amp; it’ll eventually grow to a 2.1m RCP with a cool grilled prison type room… hard yacka though.<br></div><div>“Success” was named after the group looking for it finally found it after many attempts.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
