		<Placemark id="5984C714B900003B">
			<name>Head Injuries</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Head Injuries<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.82239, 144.886875<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 42 A-10<br></div><div>LOCATION: West side of train bridge on the north bank of Stony Ck<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: Arch<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South west<br></div><div>VALUE: 😐<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Newport train to Yarraville<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Arch section<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Injuring your head<br></div><div>NEARBY: Cougar’s Tomb<br></div><div>NOTES: The name is deceptive. The injuries occurred on the first visit when Midnight Oil were popular.<br></div><div>Head Injuries gets its name due to a couple of explorers smashing their heads on low sections. The “smashes” also fitted Midnight Oil’s album of the same name.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
