			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.750421,-37.810145,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000058">
			<name>Rusco&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Rusco’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚲<br></div><div>GPS -37.963214, 145.073977<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 87 E-5<br></div><div>LOCATION: Comes out in the middle of the retarding basin. It is not the north or south drains in the basin.<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.6m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Frankston train to Cheltenham<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Fenced off. Very long!<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Getting out!<br></div><div>⛔: Wet feet<br></div><div>NEARBY: Knightstalker’s Tomb, Puppetmaster, Soggy Misui and Mosh’s Tomb<br></div><div>NOTES: It would be advantageous to chuck your bike over the fence. Rusco’s and Knightstalker’s are totally crap drains that are not worth doing!<br></div><div>Rusco’s was named after an explorer from the late 80’s/early 90’s who retired to Canberra &amp; is now growing old in Gippsland.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.073977,-37.963214,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000059">
			<name>St Kilda</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>St Kilda<br></div><div>🧠 🍸 👁<br></div><div>GPS -37.865747, 144.982395<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 2P G-8<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow canal with flow in Greeves St just north of Vale St<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: Inner<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.2m ⬜<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕ &amp; ⬜<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Sandringham train to Balaclava<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Outlet is tidal / upstream low<br></div><div>NEARBY: Albert Park, Cobra’s, Dlang &amp; Pauline’s<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS &amp; ⛔: 🙂 unless you decide to wade out at beach<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The beach<br></div><div>NOTES: Good for a laugh if you exit at the beach on a hot summer’s day.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.982395,-37.865747,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00005B">
			<name>Satan&apos;s</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Satan’s<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.752397, 145.069338<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 20 B-8<br></div><div>LOCATION: Next to the train-line near where Somers Ave meets Birchwood Ave via open section<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.9m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: A web or 2<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Eltham train to Macleod<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Grilles<br></div><div>⛔: End is grilled off<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low &amp; boring<br></div><div>NEARBY: Holey Foot &amp; Woody’s<br></div><div>NOTES: This tunnel belongs on the dung heap of all dung heaps!<br></div><div>Satan’s is not named after an old member as some newer members think, but old pre-Clan graffiti written on the wall in the pipe.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.069338,-37.725297,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00005F">
			<name>Polluted</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Polluted<br></div><div>🚫 🔑<br></div><div>GPS -37.936501, 145.141396<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 79 H-6<br></div><div>LOCATION: On the east side of Westall Rd just north of Rayhur St<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.8m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕<br></div><div>⛔: Ankle<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Build up of silt<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Massive amounts of rubbery build up &amp; junk on sides<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: The obvious<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Dandenong train to Westall<br></div><div>NEARBY: Nazi, Sandown Park &amp; Underpass<br></div><div>NOTES: The first of 6 average drains that make an OK day – Polluted, Nazi, Underpass, The Fall, Rambo &amp; Exit.<br></div><div>Polluted was named because there is huge amounts of mud build up on the walls.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.141396,-37.936501,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000060">
			<name>Pondage</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Pondage<br></div><div>🚲 🍸 🚫 ⓘ 👁 🧠 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.657813°, 144.997374°<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 8 E-1<br></div><div>LOCATION: Via a short crawly overflow (then a 1.2m drop). You’ll need to jump over a short fence to get to it from Deveny Rd.<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m RCP ⭕<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Lalor<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Overflow<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: ☹<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Outlet is waist deep with fetid water<br></div><div>NEARBY: Smee’s Tomb, Kanish’s Tomb &amp; Tic<br></div><div>NOTES: Filthy flooded outlet is located east of the listed entry point &amp; can be found here: -37.657201°, 145.001408°. Some sections are quite smelly.<br></div><div>It takes its name from the ponds located outside the drain.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.997374,-37.657813,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000062">
			<name>Punctual</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Punctual<br></div><div>🚫 🧠<br></div><div>GPS -37.819574, 145.014774<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 2H H-7<br></div><div>LOCATION: 20m north of Hawthorn Bridge on west bank of the Yarra<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: Inner<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m ⬜ room<br></div><div>VALUE: 🏆<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: Balloon &amp; ⭕<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Muddy. Wet feet<br></div><div>⛔: Ankle<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Burnley<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Slippery slide. Pointy bottom in balloon tunnel. Climbing over into/from new section. Being late.<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: First 50m<br></div><div>NEARBY: Mega Slide, CBRBD, GOD, Dight’s Falls, Vampire’s Cavern, Ladders to Heaven, No Vest, Maze and Slide<br></div><div>NOTES: Has some new really cool sections (a bit on the hardcore side). Map on page 26.<br></div><div>Punctual was named after the first expo to it was sabotaged by a lack of punctuality by members who said they’d be there.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<gx:Carousel>
