		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000063">
			<name>Rambo</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Rambo<br></div><div>🚫 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.918850, 145.168871<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 80 D-1<br></div><div>LOCATION: In the north-west corner of Freeway Reserve<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The other drain across the oval<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Westall<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low tunnel<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Underpass, Nazi, Polluted, Sandown Park, Fall and Rambo<br></div><div>NOTES: See Polluted Drain notes. Part of a group of fairly average drains, but still a good day to do.<br></div><div>When Rambo was first found there was a guy mowing a green army jacket &amp; a head-band shooting arrows into archery targets.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.168871,-37.91895,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000064">
			<name>Puppet Master</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Puppet Master<br></div><div>🚲 🍸 🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.960874, 145.074528<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 78 C-12<br></div><div>LOCATION: North east corner of Argus Street Retarding Basin<br></div><div>ZONE: South<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.7m ⭕<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Frankston train to Cheltenham<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Length<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: ☹<br></div><div>⛔: Thigh deep outlet<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Long walk back<br></div><div>NEARBY: Rusco’s Tomb, Mosh’s, 72nd &amp; Soggy Misiu<br></div><div>NOTES: Can exit via grille in a quiet street just after it shrinks, but be careful as it’s in the road. Was named by Sillogen in 2015, but Prowler did it by mistake in the 90s. Frequented by Rusco &amp; others in the 80s &amp; known as 3 Burgers &amp; a Hot Dog (the name of their drain gang) but not rated because Rusco has shit taste in drains.<br></div><div>Named by Sillogen as this drain controls other drains further downstream.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.074528,-37.960874,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000067">
			<name>Roxy&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Roxy’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫 🧠<br></div><div>GPS -37.726661, 144.825158<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 14 G-8<br></div><div>LOCATION: Just a touch downstream from Green Gully Road on the southwest bank of Taylors Ck<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.8m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North west<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to St Albans then bus to Green Gully Rd<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: 150 step stairway. Round waterfall<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low tunnel<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: ☹<br></div><div>⛔: ☹<br></div><div>NEARBY: Key Law Downs<br></div><div>NOTES: Hard yacka but well worth it.<br></div><div>Roxy was a female explorer in the Clan from 1989 till 1993 and was also besties with Dexi.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.825158,-37.726661,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000068">
			<name>Bad Air</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Bad Air<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.785965, 145.02154  MELWAYS REF: 31 A-12<br></div><div>LOCATION: South end of Yarraford Avenue<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.2m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕ (red brick)<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Gradual getting bigger!<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Hurstbridge train to Fairfield<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Maybe the odd web<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>VALUE: 😐<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low start. Starts to get bigger instantly<br></div><div>NOTES: A few features<br></div><div>NEARBY: Short, Mummy, Nam, G.O.D., Coffin, Donaldson Ck, Banger’s Tomb, Northcote Tech and Dight’s Falls<br></div><div>Bad Air took its name from the first Melbourne water “sudden flooding – bad air” sign the Clan ever saw. It was also Dougo’s first drain experience.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.02154,-37.785965,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000069">
			<name>Banger&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Banger’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫 🚲<br></div><div>GPS -37.782135, 144.991795  MELWAYS REF: 30 D-11<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow the Merri Ck downstream from Holden St<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⬜ &amp; ⭕ red-brick<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Yawning<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: South Morang train to Rushall<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Straightness<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Litter guard outside honks a bit<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Nam, Flooded, Northcote High, G.O.D., Bad Air, NGCD &amp; Dight’s Falls<br></div><div>NOTES: Stays 1.7m round and dead straight for awhile. The old section at the end was once part of G.O.D. Banger’s is actually a diversion. It is not a great drain for a bike, but a small bike will make the trip much easier.<br></div><div>Banger’s Tomb is named after a member from 1986… the fifth Beatle so to speak… but he was the fourth… and we weren’t the Beatles.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.991795,-37.782135,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00006B">
			<name>Beanz&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Beanz’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.801746, 145.358458  MELWAYS REF: 52 G-5<br></div><div>LOCATION: Corner of Moore Avenue &amp; Swansea Road, Montrose<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.1 ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⬜<br></div><div>TUNNEL ENDS: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Weird chambers<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low towards end<br></div><div>NEAREST: Leviathan<br></div><div>NOTES: Was originally known as Dengar’s Tomb<br></div><div>Beanz is named after the stat-chasing Clannie from the 90s till present.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.358458,-37.801746,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00006C">
			<name>Bell Stairway</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Bell Stairway<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.739363, 144.980339  MELWAYS REF: 18 B-12<br></div><div>LOCATION: 7 Goff St<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.6m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Upfield train to Coburg<br></div><div>⛔: Shin deep at start<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Webs &amp; wet feet<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Stairway<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Lowness<br></div><div>NEARBY: Pentridge, NGCD &amp; Ayyy Flooded<br></div><div>NOTES: Doug, with his face sticking out of a gutter box slit, had his head soaked in warm soapy water in this drain, much to the enjoyment of Rusco who screamed out the Fly On The Wall, “The wookie got flushed!”.<br></div><div>Before being explored, Bell was known as “the one near Bell Street”, and was known simply as Bell until 2014 before having Stairway added.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.980339,-37.739363,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00006D">
			<name>Big Bastard</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Big Bastard<br></div><div>🍸 ⓘ 🚲<br></div><div>GPS -37.851743, 145.053343  MELWAYS REF: 59 H-6<br></div><div>LOCATION: North East corner of Monash Freeway &amp; Burke Road intersection<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: ⌒<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Glen Waverley train to Gardiner<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Size &amp; echoes<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Flooded outlet but tunnel is short<br></div><div>NEARBY: Dougo’s Tomb, Hexadus, Sloth’s Tomb, Great Stairway &amp; Macka’s Tb<br></div><div>NOTES: A short, but good drain.<br></div><div>When Dougo first saw this drain he said to Wes, “It’s a big bastard”. Wes replied, “The cement truck?”, as there was a truck in the entrance.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.053343,-37.851743,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00006E">
			<name>Mini Tenth</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Mini Tenth<br></div><div>🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.884143, 145.090301<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 69 F-3<br></div><div>LOCATION: The southeast corner of the Monash Freeway &amp; Warrigal Road intersection<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>VALUE: 🏆<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 3m ⭕ x2<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⬜, envelope &amp; ⭕<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Size &amp; side tunnel<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: The last 25 meters is ankle deep (see notes)<br></div><div>⛔🙂 outlet end is ankle deep<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Glen Waverley train to Holmesglen then walk<br></div><div>NEARBY: Dweller’s Tomb, ID’s Tomb, Bad &amp; Howza’s Tomb<br></div><div>NOTES: Take left rectangular then explore arch, double back at flooded end and go in other rectangular tunnel on the way out &amp; check out cool side tunnel. Mini 10th is a smaller and shorter, but better, version of 10th.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
