		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00006F">
			<name>The Mission</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>The Mission<br></div><div>🚫 👣 👁<br></div><div>GPS -37.710766, 145.147436<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 21 J-4<br></div><div>LOCATION: On grounds of Judge Book Memorial Village. East bank of Diamond Ck<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m ⭕<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Finding &amp; getting down to the entrance<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Eltham<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: ☹<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Eltham, Bridgette’s, Mitchelle’s &amp; Tiffani’s<br></div><div>⛔: Once in the drain it’s 🙂<br></div><div>NOTES: Not very good, but maybe it’s better than we think? Prowler?<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.147436,-37.710766,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000071">
			<name>Mosh&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Mosh’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫 🚲<br></div><div>GPS -37.944927, 145.102236<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 73 J-8<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⬜<br></div><div>LOCATION: East side of Elder St between Davanzo Avenue &amp; Hunt Crescent<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂 ⛔🙂 (but slippery)<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Split room<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Slippery<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Dandenong train to Clayton &amp; bus to Clarinda Shopping Centre<br></div><div>NEARBY: Rusco’s Tomb, Soggy Misui, Slut’s Park, Puppetmaster and 72nd<br></div><div>NOTES: Average tunnel. Outlet may have been extended since being found? A new report would be great.<br></div><div>Mosh’s Tomb is named after the original C.C.H. explorer who was in the Cave Clan for a few years in the late 2000’s and resurfaced in the mid 2010’s.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.102236,-37.944927,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000072">
			<name>B.L.F</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>B.L.F.<br></div><div>🚫 🔑<br></div><div>GPS -37.835610, 145.172834<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 48 A-12<br></div><div>LOCATION: Upstream along creek from where Blackburn drain ends<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⭕<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: BURP-like overflows<br></div><div>⛔: knee deep outlet<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low sections between features<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Lilydale or Belgrave train to Blackburn<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Bushy getting to &amp; wet getting in<br></div><div>NEARBY: Blackburn &amp; Gets Bigger<br></div><div>NOTES: An average drain, but it has a few features for the dedicated drainer.<br></div><div>B.L.F. (1980’s union Builder’s Labourers Federation) drain was named BLF as it looked like a building site.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.172834,-37.83561,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000073">
			<name>Blue Light Disco</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Blue Light Disco<br></div><div>🔑 🚫 👁 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -38.085425, 145.464392<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 215 K-10<br></div><div>LOCATION: Henny Rd grille near linear park<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m RCP (via grille)<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car or decent walk from Pakenham Stn<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Slide<br></div><div>⛔: Ankle<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Outlet is 1m &amp; flooded<br></div><div>NEARBY: Bogan’s Lair &amp; Bogan’s Baths<br></div><div>NOTES: You can swing a large grille open here -38.088313,145.463844<br></div><div>“Thongs gave this a 🙂 but he also said ‘for out this way’.”<br></div><div>What do you think? Blue Light Disco takes its name from all the bright blue lamp posts in the area.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.464392,-38.085425,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000074">
			<name>Bob&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Bob’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫 👣 🔑<br></div><div>GPS -37.833988, 144.96838<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 2K G-2<br></div><div>LOCATION: Word of mouth<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: M/H<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕, envelope &amp; arch<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: Inner<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Getting in<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Walk from Flinders Street station<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Pumping station<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Be prepared to get wet &amp; muddy!<br></div><div>⛔: Gets deeper with the flow. Peaks at 30cms<br></div><div>NEARBY: City, South Yarra, Albert Park &amp; Melbourne<br></div><div>NOTES: The original entrance was about 100 metres upstream from the current entrance that was totally sub-merged under the Yarra. The newer entrance is grilled off &amp; can’t be entered from the outlet end. This end can be viewed from the Spencer St bridge over the Yarra. The entrance is not a secret, it’s just too hard to explain here.<br></div><div>Bob’s Tomb is named after the Gold Clannie winner. It was almost called Crown Casino drain.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.96838,-37.833988,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000079">
			<name>Big Swifty</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Big Swifty<br></div><div>🍸 🚫 👁<br></div><div>GPS -38.031290, 145.208853<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 95 C-7<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow canal north from 7A Swift Way<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.4m RCP<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Bus along Frankston–Dandenong Rd from Dandenong Stn<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Industrial runoff?<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Rooms<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔: Shin for a bit<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>NEAREST: Nongdedan<br></div><div>NOTES: Fence to the north of the drain is electrified. Canal runs through industrial area. Found by Aleph in 2015.<br></div><div>Named after Little Swift near Swift Way and from a Frank Zappa song. Found by Aleph and Iso 2015.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.208853,-38.03129,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00007A">
			<name>Blackburn</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Blackburn<br></div><div>🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.827557, 145.152413<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 47 K-12<br></div><div>LOCATION: On the northwest corner of Heath St &amp; Blackburn Rd<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2 × 1.6m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Joining rooms<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Ringwood train to Blackburn<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Awkward exit for bike<br></div><div>⛔🙂<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Just a few webs<br></div><div>NEARBY: Cro’s Tomb, Gets Bigger &amp; Fochenbeaver<br></div><div>NOTES: Not a real lot to offer. A nice lead up to Gets Bigger.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.152413,-37.827557,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00007B">
			<name>Blade&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Blade’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.900200, 145.008570<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 67 H-7<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow canal against the flow Asling St through underpass. Check side tunnel in North Rd underpass<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.8m ⬜<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>VALUE: 🏆<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Sandringham train to Gardenvale<br></div><div>⛔🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Outlet<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Tommy’s Hole, Pauline, Underworld, Cobra’s &amp; Dungeon<br></div><div>NOTES: When the tunnel splits into 2 RCPs take either as they eventually join up via a loop. See page 34 for map.<br></div><div>Blade’s Tomb was named after one of the founders of The Drain Dwellers.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.00857,-37.9002,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00007D">
			<name>Dungeon</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Dungeon
🍸 🚫 🗝️ 🌊 🚲
GPS: -37.909546, 145.019399
MELWAYS REF: 67 K-10
LOCATION: Follow canal against the flow from northwest corner of the Union Street &amp; Hawthorn Road intersection.
ENTRANCE: 2.4m ⬜
OTHER SHAPES: ⚪, ⌂, &amp; mummy.
CLAN ZONE: South.
VALUE: 🏆
TRANSPORT: Tram 64 TO Union St.
WATER: 🙂
PROBLEMS: Extremely long.
CLEANLINESS: 🙂
HIGHLIGHT: It just keeps going!
NEARBY: Blade&apos;s Tomb, Cobra&apos;s Tomb &amp; Tommy&apos;s Hole.
NOTES: Once you reach The Grille you should take the RCP on the left &amp; follow the white painted (and numbered) arrows. This way you will get the most out of the tunnel. The 2 RCP&apos;s at the outlet should be done on a separate day as, unless bikes are used, it would take too long to do it all in one day.
Dungeon is named so because of the huge grille in the roof as well as the Dungeon-like tunnels.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.019399,-37.909546,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00007E">
			<name>Dweller&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Dweller’s Tomb
🚫 🌊
GPS: -37.875146, 145.070992
MELWAYS REF: 69 B-1
LOCATION: Follow Gardiners Creek upstream from Solway St.
CLAN ZONE: East.
ENTRANCE: 2.8m ⚪
OTHER SHAPES: ⌂, ⬜ &amp; ⬜
PROBLEMS: Length.
TRANSPORT: Glen Waverley train to East Malvern.
HIGHLIGHT: Old sections. Waiting room.
CLEANLINESS: A bit wet.
WATER: Entrance is knee deep unless you can do the splits.
VALUE: 🏆
NEARBY: Chameleon, iD’s Tomb, Dougo’s Tomb, Echo Tunnel and Mini 10th.
NOTES: The entrance can be a bit off-putting to newer explorers, but on a hot day, wow! Lots of changes included. You may do a bit of slipping &amp; sliding. Don&apos;t ask about the fireman!
Dweller&apos;s Tomb is named after the group from the 80&apos;s, the Drain Dwellers. Map to the right &gt;</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.070992,-37.875146,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00007F">
			<name>Echo</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Echo
🚫 👁️
GPS: -37.867452, 145.065067
MELWAYS REF: 60 A-10
LOCATION: North of Dunlop St bridge on south-bank of Gardiners Ck
VALUE: ☹️
CLAN ZONE: East
ENTRANCE: 2.2m RCP 🎯
HIGHLIGHT: Waterfall
TRANSPORT: Glen Waverley Train to Darling
CLEANLINESS: 🙂 Once past water
WATER: Waist
PROBLEMS: Best with boat. Gets smaller quickly.
NEARBY: Chameleon, Dougo&apos;s Tomb, Dweller&apos;s, Sloth&apos;s, Great Stairway &amp; Mini 10th
NOTES: This drain was first found by Rusco in the 80’s. Nearby drains Chameleon &amp; Dwellers Tomb also have flooded outlets so a raft expo on a hot day could be fun.
The name takes its name from the cool echo that bounces off the waterfall.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.065067,-37.867452,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000080">
			<name>Howza&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>🚫 🚲
GPS: -37.893420, 145.111225
ELWAYS REF: 70 A-6
LOCATION: Just near the Osborne Ave gap.
ENTRANCE: 1.6m ⚪
OTHER SHAPES: Red brick hallway.
CLAN ZONE: South.
VALUE: ☹️
TRANSPORT: Pakenham Train to Huntingdale then bus north past Ferntree Gully Rd.
WATER: 🙂
PROBLEMS: Low.
HIGHLIGHT: Stairway.
CLEANLINESS: 🙂
NEARBY: iD&apos;s &amp; Mini Tenth
NOTES: May have another feature further on. May end at retarding basin at the SW corner of Ferntree Gully &amp; Gardiner Rds (70 E-7) -37.900745, 145.128310 although access would be unlikely.
Named after the pyjama wearing member from 2000 and teens.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.111225,-37.89342,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000081">
			<name>Idiot Box</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Idiot Box
🚫 🗝️ 🚲
GPS: -37.855761, 144.713085
MELWAYS REF: 203 A-7
LOCATION: Near the north end of Waterside Close. Build up of plants at outlet = may be deeper.
ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⚪
OTHER SHAPES: ☹️
CLAN ZONE: South west.
VALUE: 🗑️
TRANSPORT: Werribee train to Hoppers Crossing.
WATER: ☹️
PROBLEMS: Entrance has a build up due to plants outside.
HIGHLIGHT: Grilled room.
CLEANLINESS: 🙂
NEARBY: Hoppers Crossing.
NOTES: RCP joins up at grille-rooms. Do with all local drains.
Named after the movie that was not made anywhere near Hopper Crossing... even though you&apos;d swear it was.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.713085,-37.855761,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000083">
			<name>Iso&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Iso’s Tomb
🚲 🍸 🚫
GPS: -37.986673, 145.273781
MELWAYS REF: 91 H-7
LOCATION: South of Lauriston Drive x James Cook Drive roundabout.
ENTRANCE: 1.9m 🎯
CLAN ZONE: South
VALUE: ☹️
TRANSPORT: Bus 842
WATER: 🙂
PROBLEMS: The stoop to get to the feature &amp; back.
HIGHLIGHT: Double grille room linked by RCP (keep stooping)
CLEANLINESS: 🙂
NEARBY: Nongdedan.
NOTES: The double grille room is linked by a decent sized RCP so not a total shrinker.
Named after the 2016 Gold Clannie winner and team player extraordinaire. Some say his real name is Peter Sutcliff.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.273781,-37.986673,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000086">
			<name>Jub Jub&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Jub Jub’s Tomb
🚫 🚲 🍸
GPS: -37.785851, 145.309588
MELWAYS REF: 37 F-12
LOCATION: Follow Brushy Ck south from near the cnr of Sherlock Rd &amp; Felix Gve (37 E-12)
ENTRANCE: 1.8m 🎯
CLAN ZONE: East.
VALUE: 🗑️
TRANSPORT: Lilydale train to Mooroolbark.
WATER: 🙂
PROBLEMS: Low &amp; boring.
HIGHLIGHT: Split room
CLEANLINESS: 🙂
NEARBY: Leviathan.
NOTES: Okay as a lead up to Leviathan &amp; then train/car it a short distance to do Ringwood Bypass. Was originally called Mooroolbark Darkie.
Jub Jub (joined 90s) is named after the explorer that got bitch-slapped by Tress at the 2014 Clannies.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.309588,-37.785851,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA000089">
			<name>Nam</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Nam<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS: -37.784095, 145.004161<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 30 G-12<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow Merri Ck against the flow from Heidelberg Rd. Cross creek to north east bank.<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⚪<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂 below waterfall/🗑️ above waterfall.<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.6m balloon.<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Sometimes a bit webby.<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North.<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Getting by the waterfall.<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Eltham train to Westgarth.<br></div><div>WATER: Ankle.<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The first 30m up to unpassable waterfall.<br></div><div>NEARBY: Bad Air, Vampire's Cavern, Dight's Falls, GOD, Northcote High, Northcote Tech Darkies, Flooded &amp; Banger's.<br></div><div>NOTES: Tunnel can be entered via manhole above waterfall on top of cliff, however there isn't much to see above waterfall.<br></div><div>So called because of the environment surrounding the drain. Any injuries that occurred in this tunnel were reported as "Got that scar in Nam".<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.004161,-37.784095,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA00008B">
			<name>Clantomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">Clantomb 🚫 🚴 🍷</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">GPS: -37.756633, 144.934672</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">LOCATION: Just north of the Albin St bridge on the west bank</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">of Moonee Ponds Creek.</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">ENTRANCE: 3m ⭕</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">TRANSPORT: Tram 59 to Albion St</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">CLAN ZONE: North west</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">OTHER SHAPES: Mummy, ⭕ ⬜</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">HIGHLIGHTS: First 30 mins is great. Next hour is up and down.</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">PROBLEMS: Very long, boring mid section. Floods quickly.</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">CLEANLINESS: 🙂</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">NEARBY: Camo’s and 5 Mile Ck.</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">NOTES: This drain is good</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">to do if you are in the mood for a long walk underground. It</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">will take you about 90 minutes to do the whole tunnel (95% over</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">7m high). Plenty to see along the way including “Drainiac’s Graf</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">from the 1960’s”. It’s fun getting out too. During a flood Moonee</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">Ponds Ck also fills up quickly creating a double hazard!</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">Clantomb was named after the Cave Clan… in case you didn’t realise.</span></span></span><br></p><div><br></div>]]></description>
