NOTES: Refound in 2010, this drain is a real bonus for float-out expos. Originally found by Hugh Dunit in 1990. Also accessible via a grille on Swan Street across from Audi Dealership.
Novest took its name from the fact that the expo (in a boat) that rediscovered the drain was told to turn back on their Yarra float as they had &quot;no vests&quot;. If they had vests they wouldn&apos;t have turned back &amp; found the drain.</description>
