		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA0000C3">
			<name>Elisa&apos;s Tb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>🚫 🚲 🔑
GPS: -37.692935, 144.767342
MELWAYS REF: 3 C-11
LOCATION: East side of Victoria Rd at the east end of The Esplanade next to train line.
ENTRANCE: 2.2m $\odot$
CLAN ZONE: North west.
VALUE: ☹
CLEANLINESS: 🙂
WATER: $\ominus$: Shin.
TRANSPORT: Watergardens train to Watergardens.
HIGHLIGHT: Weird grilled rooms.
PROBLEMS: Tunnel was still being built when first explored so report is incomplete.
NEAREST: Bathory&apos;s Tomb.
NOTES: We would love a better more up to date report!!
Elisa&apos;s (aka Eleeasha&apos;s) is named after an explorer of the mid 90&apos;s.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.767342,-37.692935,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA0000C5">
			<name>Exit</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Exit
🚫 🚲 🍸
GPS: -37.916783, 145.167152
MELWAYS REF: 80 D-1
LOCATION: Located in the south east corner of Freeway Reserve.
ENTRANCE: 2m $\odot$
CLAN ZONE: South.
VALUE: ☹
CLEANLINESS: 🙂
WATER: $\ominus$: $\odot$
TRANSPORT: Glen Waverley train to Glen Waverley then bus to Wanda Drive.
HIGHLIGHT: Gutter boxes.
PROBLEMS: ☹
NEARBY: Underpass, Polluted, Nazi, Sandown Park, Fall &amp; Rambo.
NOTES: This tunnel is in the same reserve as Rambo Darkie and the two often get mixed up.
Exit is so called as it has many of ways out. Well it did once upon a time anyway.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.167152,-37.916783,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA0000C6">
			<name>Fall</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Fall<br></div><div>🚫 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS: -37.931552, 145.156592<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 80 A-3<br></div><div>LOCATION: East side of Springvale Road across from Faigh Street (80 A-2).<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.1m $\odot$<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South.<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>WATER: $\ominus$: $\odot$<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Glen Waverley then bus 888 to just before Princes Hwy.<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Grilled room.<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Boredom.<br></div><div>NEARBY: Underpass, Polluted, Nazi, Exit &amp; Rambo.<br></div><div>NOTES: Do with Polluted, Nazi, Exit, Underpass, Rambo &amp; Fall.<br></div><div>Fall is named after an old spray of water the used to leak from the roof.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.167152,-37.916783,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA0000C9">
			<name>F.A.R.T</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>ⓘ 🚲 $\odot$
GPS: -37.696539, 144.901181
MELWAYS REF: 6 D-12
LOCATION: Follow side creek just before inlet to BURP north-west for 150 meters.
ENTRANCE: 1.4m $\odot$
CLAN ZONE: North.
VALUE: 🗑
CLEANLINESS: $\ominus$
WATER: $\ominus$: $\odot$
TRANSPORT: Broadmeadows train to Jacana &amp; walk.
HIGHLIGHT: Waterfall.
PROBLEMS: Passing waterfall.
NEARBY: BURP, DIPS, Amebix&apos;s &amp; 172 Steps.
NOTES: Not much of a drain but a nice little prelude to BURP.
FART (Fairly Average Round Tunnel) is right near BURP.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.901181,-37.696539,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA0000CA">
			<name>Mega Slide</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Mega Slide
🚫 🧥 ⓘ
GPS: -37.810656, 145.009986
MELWAYS REF: 2H F-2
LOCATION: Under south side of footbridge where Walmer St meets the Yarra.
CLAN ZONE: Inner.
ENTRANCE: 1.3m ⚪
TRANSPORT: Any Victoria St tram to Walmer St.
VALUE: 🙂
PROBLEMS: Sliding down the slide can see you eat serious shit and end up in the Yarra.
CLEANLINESS: Slime.
HIGHLIGHT: The name sake.
WATER: ⊖: See &quot;problems&quot;.
NEARBY: CBRBD, Short, Vampire&apos;s Cavern, Dight&apos;s Falls, Ladders to Heaven, No Vest, South Yarra, Nylex, Punctual &amp; GOD.
NOTES: Not worth doing after the slide (hence the ⓘ). Is very slippery on way down. Bones may be broken!
Mega Slide is named after its feature.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.009986,-37.810656,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA0000CD">
			<name>Melton</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>ⓘ 🚲
GPS: -37.689921, 144.569752
MELWAYS REF: 336 J-10
LOCATION: Follow creek with flow from Barries Rd.
ENTRANCE: 2x2.4m ⬜
OTHER SHAPES: ☹️
CLAN ZONE: North west.
HIGHLIGHT: Entrance.
VALUE: 🗑️
PROBLEMS: The waterlevel further in.
TRANSPORT: Car.
CLEANLINESS: Starts off dry then gets deeper.
WATER: ⊖: 🙂
NEAREST: Eliza&apos;s.
NOTES: Just like the Mini 10th double rectangular tunnels but wet and rocky and um, crap!</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.569752,-37.689921,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA0000CE">
			<name>Millaria Park</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Millaria Park
🚫
GPS: -37.644926, 145.055178
MELWAYS REF: 182 J-10
LOCATION: Near the end of Cantle Close.
ENTRANCE: 1.8m 🎯
VALUE: 🗑️
HIGHLIGHT: ☹️
CLAN ZONE: North east.
TRANSPORT: Epping train to Epping.
WATER: ⊖: Waist.
CLEANLINESS: Muddy entrance.
PROBLEMS: Boring, low &amp; hard to exit.
NEARBY: Mill Park.
NOTES: Exit via crawl side tunnel. This drain had the temporary name of Mill Park Shithole for many years. The new name was going to be changed to Malaria due to the mosquito problem. In the end Millaria Park was chosen for obvious reasons.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.055178,-37.644926,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="5984C714BA0000D0">
			<name>Mini Maze</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Mini Maze
🚫 👁️
GPS: -37.777313, 144.902802
MELWAYS REF: 28 D-10
LOCATION: West side of Stanford St on grounds of Golf Course.
CLAN ZONE: North west.
VALUE: ☹️
ENTRANCE: 1.4m ⬜
OTHER SHAPES: ⌂ &amp; ⚪
WATER: ⊖: 🙂
TRANSPORT: Train to Ascot Vale.
HIGHLIGHT: There is an ok section up the left tunnel.
CLEANLINESS: Webby and muddy further up.
PROBLEMS: There is a long low loop in this tunnel that you just have to do!
NEARBY: Critt&apos;s Tomb, City View, Crime Watch &amp; Bourbon.
NOTES: Works in 2010 have made this a slightly better drain. The loop is hardcore!
A torturous low drain that had the outlet extended to make the highlight even harder to get to. Should be called Anti Maze.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.902802,-37.777313,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0F40BC9E773CA7D817F4">
			<name>Anzac</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">G.O.D. ⬜ 🚫 🧗</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">GPS: 37.795754, 145.001252</span></span></spa