				<Placemark id="FCB5B6402853CFB0CB3D6">
					<name>Debris / 1924</name>
					<snippet></snippet>
					<description><![CDATA[Description:   A big-small-big-small-big-small-big drain that is a mix of very
               old and newer sections. MPL=450m. TEL=450m.
Features:      Old chambers (8'), with sandstone floors, walls and concrete
               ceilings that still have the rendering newspaper stuck to them.
               The newspaper is readable and all dated 1924, highly amusing
               advertorial and editorial articles. D/s end is 5' waterfalls,
               knee deep GPT, then tidal exit to Cooks River.
Access:        #0,UE: Running d/s from rail embankment on Ewart St near Ewart
               Lane [Sw:295R16, UBD:254J12, Grg:373D12,
               [GPS:-33.9102473133,151.139014373]]. U/s is "Debris". When
               intending to go beyond the 2nd GPT, use the left tunnel, as the
               water depth is shallower that side of the GPT. 
               #9,AX: Cooks River.
Locality:      Dulwich Hill
Region:        NSW
Country:       Australia
Care:          Low tide only.
Water Level:   Tidal, Shin-Chest. Has CDS installed so sections may be flooded
Nearby:        *Course: Debris == 1924 ==<Cooks River.
Found:         1998 Siologen/Dirge.
Rating:        2.0/5.0]]></description>
