			<name>Soggy Misiu</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Soggy Misiu<br></div><div>GPS -37.972028, 145.110303<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 88 A-3<br></div><div>LOCATION: Enter canal north side of Centre Dandenong Rd<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.7m ⬜<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car or 828 bus from Dandenong Station<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Large grille room<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: 👁 Very visible from road, but no one is likely to care much<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Rusco’s Tomb, Mosh’s Tomb &amp; Puppetmaster<br></div><div>NOTES: Drain likely to be extended.<br></div><div>Named after a soggy misiu was found on the first visit. Misiu is Polish for teddy bear.<br></div>]]></description>
