		<Placemark id="9A5BB5B6F03E4617280A">
			<name>Five Mile Creek</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Five Mile Creek<br></div><div>GPS -37.746835, 144.926453<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 28 J-2<br></div><div>LOCATION: Behind restaurant at 314 Pascoe Vale Rd<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.9m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⬜<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North west<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: A bit webby<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: End of Part A<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂🗑<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: A bit awkward getting in<br></div><div>⛔ Outlet is wide but avoidable<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Craigieburn train to Glenbervie<br></div><div>NEARBY: Burbon, Critter’s Tomb, Crime Watch, Clantomb, Fox Hole &amp; Camo’s Tomb<br></div><div>NOTES: Once you exit via the dungeon-like stairway, follow the canal on past the train lines and you will find the less than impressive part B.<br></div>]]></description>
