		<Placemark id="121117DA3DB3E4617280A">
			<name>Woody&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Woody’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.730477, 145.040614<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 19 E-9<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow Darebin Ck east bank from Dougharty Rd against the flow for ten minutes<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.2m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Bus<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: OK<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Keeping feet dry at outlet<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Lake overflow &amp; exit<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂 or ankle of lazy<br></div><div>NEARBY: Satan’s, Forgotten &amp; Northlands<br></div><div>NOTES: Good (obvious) exit through side tunnel. Was duck and turtle trap until the Cave Clan reported to the Humane Society and a safety net was placed over the lake overflow.<br></div><div>Woody’s Tomb is named after one of the founders of the Cave Clan. He also allegedly rooted poor cats.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.040614,-37.730477,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="1494DDCA4DF3E4617280A">
			<name>Mira&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Mira’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.565733, 143.866557<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.4m ⬜<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>LOCATION: Corner of Eastwood &amp; Barkly Sts<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: 🎈 balloon, various ⬜ ⬜ &amp; mummy<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Old style tunnels<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ Ankle<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Ballarat<br></div><div>NEARBY: Ballarat &amp; Mouse Hole<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Balloon section is ankle deep<br></div><div>NOTES: A nice drain even if it is low and slippery in parts. A good lead up to Ballarat drains.<br></div><div>Named after the Cave Clan member from Melbourne that starred in the Clan in the 90’s and naughties.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>143.866557,-37.565733,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="04F82A827E3E4617280B">
			<name>Three Sisters</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Three Sisters<br></div><div>🚫 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.680515, 144.937327<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 7 B-7<br></div><div>LOCATION: Weird sections all found at the south end of Dallas Drive in retarding basin<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: Various ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔ Ankle<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Craigieburn train to Broadmeadows<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Mini BURP, drain &amp; more<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Two of the three are ☹<br></div><div>NEARBY: COAD &amp; 172 Steps<br></div><div>NOTES: OK, if you are nearby. Use bike only to get to the locations.<br></div><div>The 3 Sisters combines 3 short sections of drain that add up to an OK location.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.937327,-37.680515,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="11662D58353E4617280B">
			<name>Tic</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Tic<br></div><div>🚫 🔑<br></div><div>GPS -37.643363, 144.964118<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 180 H-9<br></div><div>LOCATION: East end of Fleet St on Freight Drive<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.2m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Not much since they took away the stairway inlet ☹<br></div><div>⛔ Neck deep entrance<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Muddy in parts<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Flooded entrance<br></div><div>NEARBY: Grilles in the Mist, Pondage, Tac &amp; Toe<br></div><div>NOTES: This should be your first of 3 including Tac &amp; Toe.<br></div><div>If stuck in Grilles in the Mist &amp; you’ve got yourself one crap day of draining.<br></div><div>Use manhole on Filo Dve just north of Fleet St to enter -37.642439, 144.957475<br></div><div>Tic, Tac and Toe were all found on the same day.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.964118,-37.643363,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="3DEEC5FB9F3E4617280B">
			<name>Toe</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Toe<br></div><div>🚫 🔑<br></div><div>GPS -37.623451, 144.95231<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 180 E-4<br></div><div>LOCATION: East end of Patullos Lane behind the recycling depot<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.5m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Room<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Slippery entrance<br></div><div>⛔ May be deeper now? 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Grilles in the Mist, COAD, Funnel Web’s Lair, Tic &amp; Tac<br></div><div>NOTES: Entrance is in dense bush. Iso said “Had THE WORST drain water I’d ever seen at last check (early 2016) – was the consistency &amp; smell of vomit, probably mix of rubbish tip runoff and illegal sewer hook-ups (and Dezi’s spew). May have been reported to the EPA, so might be better now.”<br></div><div>Tic, Tac &amp; Toe were all found on the same day.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.95231,-37.623451,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="51092062413E4617280B">
			<name>Tricky&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Tricky’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.773685, 145.187177<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 34 H-9<br></div><div>LOCATION: Near north-west end of Baradine Tce (north-east side)<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.5m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Size change<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Boring<br></div><div>NEAREST: Guinea Pig’s Tomb<br></div><div>NOTES: Once in, it will get smaller (1.9m) then bigger (2.2m).<br></div><div>Tricky’s Tomb is named after the Clan member that was mates with Seannie.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.187177,-37.773685,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="BCE27309643E4617280B">
			<name>NGCD</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>NGCD<br></div><div>🚲 🚫 🍸 👁<br></div><div>GPS -37.75976, 144.986848<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 30 C-5<br></div><div>LOCATION: West end of Woolton Ave in golf course just near fence<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>VALUE: 🏆<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.9m ⬜ + 2.2m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⬜ &amp; ⬜<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Cross pipes at head height<br></div><div>⛔ 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Northcote High, Banger’s Tomb, Flooded &amp; Bell Stairway<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The pillars<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: South Morang train to Croxton<br></div><div>NOTES: This drain was HQ for the Clan for their first few years. The Pillars was the original meeting place for drain explorers throughout the 80’s. This drain was also where tragedy struck on 22/12/2000 when Brian McHugh tragically drowned.<br></div><div>It is named after the golf course located at the outlet.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
