		<Placemark id="1C6B92C292E3E4617280B">
			<name>Funnel Web&apos;s Lair</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Funnel Web’s Lair<br></div><div>🚫 🔑 👁<br></div><div>GPS -37.639755, 144.920798<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 179 F12<br></div><div>LOCATION: Via gate on south side of Somerton Rd in park east of Magnolia Blvd<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.9m dry ⭕ overflow<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: This section of 150 meters or so of tunnel has a couple of highlights<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: A few splashes<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Locked gate. Do via Funnel Web if you are hardcore (and mental)<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Funnel Web’s Lair, Tac, Toe, COAD &amp; Grilles in the Mist<br></div><div>NOTES: Without spoiling too much of this little bonus section of drain, here are some directions – if you can make it by the locked gate then follow the tunnel until you get to the fork. Turn left (to the right is Funnel Web &amp; you DO NOT want to go down there!), and you will soon come to its namesake. Do in daylight for best value. A good photo op if someone is prepared to wait outside.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.920798,-37.639755,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="209DFA74DCA3E4617280B">
			<name>TWL</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>TWL<br></div><div>ⓘ<br></div><div>GPS -37.782800, 144.939887<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 29 B-12<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow east side of Moonee Ponds Ck against the flow from Mount Alexander Rd under Tullamarine Fwy<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.2m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: Mummy<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North west<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Shape change<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Wet entrance<br></div><div>VALUE: 😐<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Upfield train to Flemington Bridge<br></div><div>⛔: Shin deep at start<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Waterlevel<br></div><div>NEARBY: 69er<br></div><div>NOTES: A lake was created that made the inlet thigh deep, then due to the Tullamarine/Westgate Freeway extension, the entrance is now deep. The entrance is located under the freeway and has a short part two that can be found a bit further upstream.<br></div><div>TWL was called Moonee Ponds Ck, but as it was only a tributary of the creek its name was changed after TWL bridge 300m upstream.<br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.939267,-37.7828,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="263C6FE945E3E4617280B">
			<name>Karmein&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Karmein’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫 🚲<br></div><div>GPS -37.691421, 145.008936<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 8 G-11<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow east side of Edgars Ck against flow for about 10 mins from Mahoneys Rd bridge<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Entrance<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: South Morang train to Keon Park<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low &amp; boring<br></div><div>NEARBY: Kanish’s, Stormdrain 2000 &amp; Edgar’s<br></div><div>NOTES: Was called Thomastown until human remains were found buried outside.<br></div><div>Karmein is named in memory of a murder victim found nearby and not a member of the Cave Clan.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.008936,-37.691421,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="284EB02FF413E4617280B">
			<name>Knightstalker&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Knightstalker’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚲<br></div><div>GPS -38.001585, 145.096024<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 87 H-11<br></div><div>LOCATION: South end of Manikato Ave. Ends at Rusco’s Tomb Retarding basin<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.6m ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: ☹<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Webby<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Frankston train to Mordialloc<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Lowness &amp; length<br></div><div>NEARBY: Rusco’s &amp; Big Ears<br></div><div>NOTES: This drain is not all that impressive. Do after Rusco’s Tomb… if you can really be bothered.<br></div><div>Knightstalker’s was named after the Clan member from the 80’s (ex-Vampire). Originally beyond the envelope section in Mini Tenth was Knightstalker’s Tomb before works on the Monash Freeway saw it become part of Mini 10th.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.096024,-38.001585,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="29136E972673E4617280B">
			<name>Ladders To Heaven</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Ladders To Heaven<br></div><div>🚫 👁<br></div><div>GPS -37.813850, 145.014644<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 2H H-4<br></div><div>LOCATION: South of Victoria St bridge on west bank of Yarra River<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: Inner<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.3m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Bridge Rd or Victoria St trams to the Yarra<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The ladder rooms<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: You’ll get a bit dirty<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Slippery when wet<br></div><div>NEARBY: Mega Slide, CBRBD, GOD, Dight’s Falls, Vampire’s Cavern, Punctual, No Vest, Maze &amp; Slide<br></div><div>NOTES: Do before Punctual and Mega Slide to make it a more worthwhile day.<br></div><div>Ladders to Heaven is self explanatory… depending on what you think heaven is.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.014644,-37.81385,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="2A0CF10BE8E3E4617280B">
			<name>Lalo</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Lalor<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.675882, 145.04147<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 9 E-6<br></div><div>LOCATION: North of the McKimmies Rd bridge on the northwest bank of Darebin Ck. Next to 71 McKimmies Rd<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.9m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>⛔: Shin deep<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: South Morang train to Thomastown then bus<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: The short water pit<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Entrance has pit of water<br></div><div>NEARBY: Mill Park, Bundoora &amp; Bundpoora<br></div><div>NOTES: I would not bother! All nearby drains are total shit!<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.04147,-37.675882,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="2B94895BEA63E4617280B">
			<name>Dlang</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Dlang<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.866802, 144.990174<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 2P G-8<br></div><div>LOCATION: Follow canal upstream from inlet to St Kilda Darkie (better location required)<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: Inner<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: ⬜<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ?<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Any St Kilda Rd tram to Carlisle St<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: ?<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Low<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: ☹<br></div><div>NEARBY: Albert Park, St Kilda, Pauline &amp; Cobra’s<br></div><div>NOTES: It’s been more than 20 years since the author last did this drain.<br></div><div>This drain has been known as St Kilda B and was renamed after local drainer Dlang who passed away in 2017.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.990174,-37.866802,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="2E594DC1BDB3E4617280B">
			<name>Donaldson Creek</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Donaldson Creek<br></div><div>🚫 👁<br></div><div>GPS -37.769329, 145.036227<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 31 D-8<br></div><div>LOCATION: South side of Della Torre Cres between Shaw St &amp; Kenilworth Pde or via open section across the road<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.4m &amp; 1.8 ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⌒<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Open section<br></div><div>⛔: Left tunnel is flooded<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Eltham train to Darebin station<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Boring after highlight. House built looking over outlet<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Dry tunnel is muddy<br></div><div>NEARBY: Bad Air, Northcote Tech, Forgotten &amp; Coffin<br></div><div>NOTES: Not worth passing open section other than a pizza sized hole in roof that leads to an underpass.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.036227,-37.769329,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="09961A508B3E4617280C">
			<name>Dougo&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Dougo’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚫<br></div><div>GPS -37.853695, 145.061038<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 60 B-6<br></div><div>LOCATION: 11A Denman Av (approx). Follow Back Creek with the flow from Sloth’s Tomb<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 3.2 ⬜<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⌒<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>VALUE: 🏆<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Alamein train to Hartwell<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Entrance<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Good except for the outlet<br></div><div>⛔: Outlet knee<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Exiting<br></div><div>NEARBY: Great Stairway, Echo Tunnel, Macka’s, Hexadus, Chameleon, Big Bastard &amp; Sloth’s<br></div><div>NOTES: The 1.6 side pipe has some nice bits for hardcore explorers. Do Dougo’s then Sloth’s and Great Stairway.<br></div><div>Dougo’s Tomb is named after one of the founding Clan members who is also rumoured to be an iron-fisted wookie who has murdered some members.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<gx:Carousel>
				<gx:Image kml:id="hosted_image__0">
