		<Placemark id="3C6A0164103E4617280C">
			<name>Sandown Park</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Sandown Park<br></div><div>🧠 👁<br></div><div>GPS -37.943818, 145.170825<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 80 E-7<br></div><div>LOCATION: Via walking path at end of Brough St (D-7). Only end is flooded.<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⭕<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⬜<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Dandenong train to Sandown Park<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Hall<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Little bit messy<br></div><div>NEARBY: MWOTH, Rambo, Polluted, Nazi, Underpass, Fall &amp; Exit<br></div><div>⛔: Deep end<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Part B is awkward<br></div><div>NOTES: This section is quite short. Once you reach the end of part A, follow the creek with the flow to part B which ends in the middle of Sandown Park raceway which can be very hard to exit 👁<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.170825,-37.942818,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="504719E6F33E4617280C">
			<name>72nd</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>72nd<br></div><div>🚫 🧠 🔑<br></div><div>GPS -37.999974, 145.07979<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 78 D-6<br></div><div>LOCATION: North-west corner of retarding basin located at east end of Wren Road on Warrigal Road<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.8m ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: The entrance<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Large fence on a main road<br></div><div>⛔: Ankle/shin deep<br></div><div>NEARBY: Mosh’s, Puppetmaster &amp; Rusco’s<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Dandenong train to Oakleigh then bus south along Warrigal Rd<br></div><div>NOTES: This drain may still flow into Puppetmaster via a crawl tunnel. See previous page for map.<br></div><div>72nd was the seventy second tunnel the Cave Clan explored… hey, we couldn’t think of a name, ok!<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.07979,-37.939974,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="65F1A39A063E4617280C">
			<name>Short</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Short<br></div><div>ⓘ 🚲<br></div><div>GPS -37.739139, 145.031881<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 45 C-1<br></div><div>LOCATION: Downstream from Mummy located just as the river &amp; the bike track separate<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.6m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Waterfalls<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Eltham train to Alphington then walk<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Entrance deep after heavy rain<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Webby<br></div><div>NEARBY: Glass Creek Triplets, Glass Ck, Mummy, Bad Air, Donaldson Ck &amp; Coffin<br></div><div>NOTES: You can take your bike but you will have to leave it at the waterfall so it’s pointless. A good short drain. See map on page 24.<br></div><div>Short is so named because it is a short tunnel (brrrrr).<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.031881,-37.790139,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="77FC6BC1B73E4617280C">
			<name>POD</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>POD<br></div><div>🚫 🔑<br></div><div>GPS -37.788928, 145.209192 (?)<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 49 C-1<br></div><div>LOCATION: Find gated dirt track in the valley of Alder Crt. Follow 200m to entrance. Look for grille along track.<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>⛔: Waist<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Ramps<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car or bus<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Entrance muddy<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Flooded entrance<br></div><div>NEARBY: Ringwood Bypass<br></div><div>NOTES: POD is in this little secret valley kind of thing in the bush. I think the entrance might even be way down the back of someone’s yard as there’s a gazebo &amp; sitting area next to it. We got in via a small grille about maybe 100 metres from the entrance, stuffed if I could describe exactly where that is but it should be fairly easy to find. It’s maybe a bit over 2 metres from memory. Green.<br></div><div>Name stands for Park Orchard Darkie.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.209192,-37.788928,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="AE9C52EC6E3E4617280C">
			<name>Porridge</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Porridge<br></div><div>🚫 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.890769, 144.687836<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 206 F-5<br></div><div>LOCATION: Go through underpass at corner of Princes Highway &amp; Georgia Crescent<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South west<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.3m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Grilled room<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Werribee train to Hoppers Crossing<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Piggery, Werribee Slide &amp; CPND<br></div><div>NOTES: Do the Hoppers Crossing trio. The entrance once had a unique double metal door.<br></div><div>Porridge is so named due to the 2 gates that covered the entrance that were covered in chains resembling a prison.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.687836,-37.890769,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="EC29639C023E4617280C">
			<name>Rieschiecks</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Rieschicks<br></div><div>🚫 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.778394, 145.14475<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 33 J-10<br></div><div>LOCATION: At the west end of Muriel Green Drive on the west side of Victoria St<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>VALUE: 🗑<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.7m ⭕<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Boring shrinker<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Bus or car<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Classic RCP entrance<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Flat &amp; Bumboys<br></div><div>NOTES: There are some other average shrinkers to be found downstream as well as the nice overflow known as Bumboy’s with its big rooms &amp; lots of fish. -37.772757, 145.135137<br></div><div>Rieschicks is named after the park it runs under.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.14475,-37.778394,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="FA080AFE623E4617280C">
			<name>Ringwood Bypass</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Ringwood Bypass<br></div><div>🚲 🍸 ⓘ<br></div><div>GPS -37.809928, 145.233421<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF. 49 J-7<br></div><div>LOCATION: Located near the north-west end of Suda Ave<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 3× 3m / 5m ⬜<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North east<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Big &amp; dry tunnels<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to Ringwood &amp; walk<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Getting to lake overflow is low<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Chastity Belt and POD<br></div><div>NOTES: Ringwood Lake Overflow can be found up the main side pipe. Cleanliness &amp; Waterlevel do not include pipe to overflow. Main tunnel is short. Do only if you are in the area, there may be new stuff in area due to new roads.<br></div><div>Ringwood Bypass runs under the road that it takes its name from.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
