		<Placemark id="13CDF2B05C93E4617280C">
			<name>Bathory&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Bathory’s Tomb<br></div><div>🚲 🔑 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.736758, 144.763018  MELWAYS REF: 13 B-11<br></div><div>LOCATION: Near west side of Kinterbury Drive on east bank of Kororoit Creek<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North west<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2.4m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>VALUE: 😐<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Length (including Part B)<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Getting bike through wet start<br></div><div>⛔: Shin<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Train to St Albans then bus along Main Road West<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Wet entrance<br></div><div>NEARBY: Alien’s Tomb &amp; Yabbie<br></div><div>NOTES: Bike for Part B<br></div><div>Bathory’s Tomb was named after a Gold Clannie winning member from the 1990s and not the heavy metal band.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.763018,-37.736758,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="1DEC1C3982A3E4617280C">
			<name>Bogan&apos;s Baths</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Bogan’s Baths<br></div><div>🔑 👁<br></div><div>GPS -38.061870, 145.456376<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 215 J-4<br></div><div>LOCATION: Grille &amp; 10m crawl. Princes Hwy south of Bunnings Car Park<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.6m RCP<br></div><div>VALUE: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Car or decent walk from Cardinia Rd Station<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Overflow structures<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔: Ankle<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Grille entrance is bolted<br></div><div>NEARBY: Bogan’s Lair &amp; Blue Light Disco<br></div><div>NOTES: The bolts on the entrance grille can be undone by finger. There is a part B but accessing this area is a problem.<br></div><div>Originally called Deni’s Love Tunnel, renamed Bogan’s Baths by Thongs due to its proximity to Bogan’s Lair.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.456376,-38.06187,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="1EC6D48BD6E3E4617280C">
			<name>Bogan&apos;s Lair</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Bogan’s Lair<br></div><div>🚫 🔑 🚲 🍸<br></div><div>GPS -38.073521, 145.486458<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 317 E-8<br></div><div>LOCATION: Opposite 10 King St<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m ⭕<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ☹<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: East<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Pakenham train to Pakenham<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Unique exit<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: 🙂<br></div><div>⛔🙂<br></div><div>NEAREST: Bogan’s Baths &amp; Blue Light Disco<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Getting bike out of exit<br></div><div>NOTES: This tunnel has a few grilled rooms but when you get to the end grille, go back in the pipe a few meters and take the side tunnel to the grilled room… crazy exit! If grille in underpass is locked, grille in flowpath is openable (crawl ~10 metres).<br></div><div>Bogan’s Lair was named for the boganish graffiti written in and around the tunnel.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.486458,-38.073521,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="1F98F3C0E173E4617280C">
			<name>Bourbon</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Bourbon / Critter’s Tomb<br></div><div>🍸<br></div><div>GPS -37.76516, 144.901788<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 28 D-7<br></div><div>LOCATION: Corner of Holmes Road and The Boulevard on the northeast bank of the Maribyrnong River<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 2m arch<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: North west<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: Wet feet &amp; very webby<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: There is a GPT located inside the entrance that you must walk through<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Craigieburn train to Moonee Ponds<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Rare shapes or easier access to Critter’s Tomb<br></div><div>⛔🙂☹<br></div><div>VALUE: 🙂<br></div><div>NEARBY: Critter’s, Mini Maze, Camo’s, Clantomb, Vegie &amp; Crime Watch<br></div><div>NOTES: Bourbon &amp; Critters were found at the same time many years ago but Crit’s, due to the low &amp; often flooded outlet, wasn’t done until a year later. Both drains were given individual names before we realised that they are joined by 2 overflows. Sometimes described as a wishbone drain where one system splits &amp; has two outlets.<br></div><div>When Bourbon was first spotted the location wasn’t recorded. When the Clan returned to explore it, it couldn’t be found. A Nightmare On Elm Street 3 was on at the time. A line in the movie was, “Where’s the fucken bourbon bitch!?” We were asking, “Where’s the fucken drain bitch!?”<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.901788,-37.76516,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="201D2DBD1BA3E4617280C">
			<name>Big Ear&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<div>Big Ear’s Tomb<br></div><div>👥<br></div><div>GPS -38.000197, 145.075085<br></div><div>MELWAYS REF: 87 C-11<br></div><div>LOCATION: On beach opposite Parkers Road<br></div><div>ENTRANCE: 1.4m ⬜<br></div><div>OTHER SHAPES: ⭕ &amp; ⬜<br></div><div>⏱: Tidal<br></div><div>CLAN ZONE: South<br></div><div>CLEANLINESS: A bit muddy at start<br></div><div>HIGHLIGHT: Unique tunnel<br></div><div>TRANSPORT: Frankston train to Parkdale<br></div><div>VALUE: 🏆<br></div><div>PROBLEMS: Waves at outlets. First 30 mins is boring<br></div><div>NEARBY: Knightstalker’s<br></div><div>NOTES: Another great, except for a short section of rectangular, round drain. Do this tunnel on a hot day as you will actually want to get wet a bit at the beach. You can still enter with just getting wet up to your shins when the tide is good if you are lucky. After 30 minutes you’ll come to a junction. Follow the marked tunnel (left?) &amp; soon you’ll have to crawl for a couple of minutes. From this point on, it’s a ball! Alternatively do it with people who know the best manhole to enter from to get the most out of the goodness.<br></div><div>Big Ear’s is named after the member that was active throughout the late 90’s and 2000’s and not today’s best friend.<br></div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0920FA33F53E916505AE</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>145.075085,-38.000197,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="24CD3B5FE8A3E4617280C">
			<name>Drongo&apos;s Den</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description><![CDATA[<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">Drongo’s Den ⭕ 🚴 🍷</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">GPS: -37.756936, 145.112975</span></spa