man&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal; min-height: 13.8px;"><br></p><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; font-width: normal; font-size: 19px; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-feature-settings: normal; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-variation-settings: normal;"><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-kerning: none;"><span class="font" style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 19px;">NOTES: Drain that doesn’t have a lot, but became slightly better after a new grilled room was added in late 1990s. Originally named Finn's after the reserve where the outlet was found, the drain has been renamed due to being frequented by drain drongo's&nbsp;</span></span></span><br></p><div><br></div>]]></description>
