		<Placemark id="096888741E3E4617280D">
			<name>MWOTH</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>MWOTH
🚫 👁️
GPS: -37.967747, 145.193829
MELWAYS REF: 89 K 2
LOCATION: Where Yarraman Ck heads underground just south of the Heatherton Road overpass next to bike path.
ENTRANCE: 2m ⚪ x 2
OTHER SHAPES: ☹️
CLAN ZONE: South.
HIGHLIGHT: Large junction room.
TRANSPORT: Train to Yarraman &amp; bike or walk.
CLEANLINESS: Muddy &amp; webby.
WATER: Knee
PROBLEMS: Unpassable waterfall.
NEARBY: Sandown Park &amp; Nongdedan.
VALUE: 🙂
NOTES: The addition of a rope ladder at the waterfall = good. Originally known as Mad Max&apos;s Drains after a gunman that supposedly hid in them in 1989 (he didn&apos;t). Upstream section can be accessed via grille on Heyington Cr at 81 A12 -37.961694, 145.198112
The system was extended during construction of the East Link freeway and became known as MWOTH (My Way Or The Highway) after local kids used the underpass, before the drain was extended, as a short cut to go to cheap-arse Tuesday movies.</description>
