LOCATION: Behind Fanny Reserve located on the corner of Fanny &amp; Salisbury Streets.
CLAN ZONE: North west.
ENTRANCE: 1.9m ⚪
OTHER SHAPES: ⌂
CLEANLINESS: webs.
PROBLEMS: Slippery in parts.
WATER: ☹️
HIGHLIGHT: Old sections around waterfall.
VALUE: 🙂
TRANSPORT: Tram 59 to first stop after Wilson Street.
NEARBY: Clantomb, TWL, Burbon &amp; Critter’s &amp; 5 Mile Ck.
NOTES: Instead of turning at the bottom of the waterfall the drain continued straight to Moonee Ponds Ck. The cement section was added during the 70&apos;s. The ladder at the waterfall was added in 1996. There is a manhole exit that exits just across the road from a police station. See middle and left maps below.
Camo’s Tomb was named after the explorer from the mid to late 1980’s who joined the Clan from The Drain Dweller’s along with Cobra &amp; Blade.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_088AD2C4923E916505AD</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.934169,-37.760618,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="2EEB1094BD53E4617280D">
			<name>Slasha&apos;s Tomb</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Slasha&apos;s Tomb
🚫 🚲 🍸
GPS: -37.753954, 144.819869
MELWAYS REF: 26 E-4
LOCATION: Near the north-east corner of Moonstone Circuit.
ENTRANCE: 1.7m 🎯
CLAN ZONE: North West.
VALUE: 🗑️
WATER: Ankle.
TRANSPORT: Watergardens train to Ginifer.
CLEANLINESS: Muddy sections.
HIGHLIGHT: Probably the entrance.
PROBLEMS: Muddy entrance.
NEARBY: Yabbie, Jones Ck Outlet, Not 50th, 50th &amp; C.I.T.
NOTES: Left tunnel is the best. This tunnel was not thoroughly explored.
Slasha&apos;s was named after the ex-Vampire come Cave Clanner from the late 80&apos;s early 90&apos;s who sat in Mad Rat&apos;s vomit in &apos;89.</description>
			<styleUrl>#__managed_style_05D0D2A5813E916505B0</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>144.819869,-37.753954,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="1EE0BA10F03E4617280E">
			<name>Slut&apos;s Park</name>
			<snippet></snippet>
			<description>Slut&apos;s Park
🍸
GPS: -37.934881, 145.114321
MELWAYS REF: 79 A-5
LOCATION: In wetlands near Russ St.
ENTRANCE: 2 OR 3 ⚪
OTHER SHAPES: ☹️
CLAN ZONE: South.
VALUE: 🗑️
WATER: Mostly 🙂
TRANSPORT: Train to Clayton.
CLEANLINESS: 🙂
HIGHLIGHT: The Back-story of the name.
PROBLEMS: The let down of the quality.
NEARBY: Polluted and Mosh&apos;s Tomb.
NOTES: Found by A&amp;A Drain Team in the 80s, but didn&apos;t excite anyone. &quot;Discovered&quot; by Panic 20 years later and described as &quot;a new huge good drain&quot;.
Slut&apos;s Park was named by the A&amp;A Drain Team after some of the locals that frequented the park where the drain was located.</description>
