			<description>Cougar&apos;s Tomb
GPS: -37.80839, 144.899971
MELWAYS REF: 42 D-7
LOCATION: East side of Hyde St on the cnr of Lyons St.
CLAN ZONE: South west.
ENTRANCE: 1.3m ⬜
VALUE: 🙂
OTHER SHAPES: Gothic ⬜ &amp; ⚪
WATER: Ankle.
PROBLEMS: Low section at start.
TRANSPORT: Williamstown train to Seddon.
CLEANLINESS: You may slip if your feet get wet.
HIGHLIGHT: Gets bigger/unique shape.
NEARBY: City View, 69er &amp; Head Injuries.
NOTES: Lowness makes this drain a bit awkward at first, but never judge a book by its cover! New works in part B. Known as Footscray Main Drain on map below.
Cougar&apos;s (late 80&apos;s) is a member of BDP. RfP</description>
